<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB/12–1346: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the United States Representative at the United
                                Nations</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-13T18:00:00-05:00">December
                                    13, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>319. <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USdel</gloss>. Dept most anxious that Siam
                            be admitted to membership in UN at this session <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. Please make every effort expedite procedure to this
                                end.<note n="65" xml:id="d250fn65">The resolution admitting Siam to
                                membership in the United Nations was adopted unanimously by the
                                General Assembly at the last plenary meeting of the Session on
                                December 15 (<gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> (I/2), <hi rend="italic">Plenary</hi>, pp. 1458 and 1459).</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>